(83, 4, 72, 0, 42, 'none'),
(84, 4, 73, 0, 42, 'An antique baby blue lacquered low cabinet with 2 doors and 3 drawers dated c.1930 from Dongbei Province. Full of character and charm, beautifully restored with a touch of light blue glossay lacquer to allow original wooden courlors shimmering through, this characteristic low cabinet would make a fantastic hallway bench with planty of storage/organiser space, a charming cloakroom shoe stand, or a playroom bench.'),
(85, 4, 72, 0, 43, 'none'),
(86, 4, 73, 0, 43, 'A wooden stool with a soft deged circular seat originated in Beijing. Beautifully hand crafted in Chinese pine wood with four square shaped legs and crossbar strtcher detail.     This worker''s stool was made using traditional Oriental mortise and tenon joinery and has been finished with a blue distressed lacquer.'),
(87, 4, 72, 0, 44, 'none'),
(88, 4, 73, 0, 44, 'A pleasingly curvaceous round table with detaled stand. Full of character and charm, with a cracled glaze blue, green and brown lacquer finish and stunning durable surface  this table is a comnination of function and sculptual beauty.     This gorgeous table could make a great small dining or an eye-catching occational table.'),
(89, 4, 72, 0, 45, 'none'),
