(93, 4, 72, 0, 47, 'none'),
(94, 4, 73, 0, 47, 'A striking blue lacquer antique cabinet from the Gansu province of China dated c.1930. Beasutifully resored, this solid wood cabinet has two doors and an eye-catching distressed look.      With a dominant blue look this piece also has a multitude of other colours within it showing the layers of history through its crackle glaze lacquer.     Full of character and charm, with a deep cupboard, original handpainted decorative doors and solid legs this piece of anique cabinet will efforlessly add a touch of colour and interesting history to any space of interior design.'),
(95, 4, 72, 0, 48, 'none'),
